news.title: Nashik civic body adds stricter tree-plantation clause in new real estate policy
news.para: The Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) has drafted a new policy for real estate developers undertaking construction activities in the city. The move is aimed at increasing the city’s green cover.

news.title: Developers in Rajasthan demand reduction in labour cess penalty
news.para: As per rule, the project owners are required to pay BOCW cess of 1% for construction of a building costing more than Rs 10 lakh, within one month after completion. If they don’t deposit the amount, they would be liable to pay a cess of 2% per month.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh to construct 8.6 lakh new houses under PMAY-Rural
news.para: The Centre has approved Rs 10,000 crore for the construction of houses under the scheme, on the basis of a proposal submitted by the UP Government. The houses are expected to be ready by March 2024.

news.title: No OC issued for your building in Gurugram? Apply online before Dec 31
news.para: According to HSVP, they have found that a considerable number of residential, commercial and institutional properties have been occupied without valid certificates.

news.title: Gurugram: No work at site for 1.5 years, buyers seek Expressway Tower's audit
news.para: The project was launched on seven acres of land in 2017 with a four-year deadline. However, only 60% of the work has been done to date. Currently, no work is going on at the site and most of the homebuyers have paid almost 90% of the flat cost.

news.title: Gurugram: Court denies anticipatory bail to Ardee City's builder in land fraud cases
news.para: Denying the application of Gopal Das Estates & Housing director Shibani Verma Kapur, additional sessions judge Jasbir Singh observed that the charges were serious and taking such offences “lightly” would be an “injustice”.

news.title: SC asks MHADA for status of FIRs on builders, surplus area
news.para: An order by an SC bench of Justices M R Shah and M M Sundresh seeking details of surplus area surrendered by builders and the status of FIRs in 246 projects has put Mhada in a bind.

news.title: China Evergrande gives back 332.4 acres land to Jiangxia district
news.para: The government of Jiangxia District in the central city of Wuhan retrieved its land-use rights over the undeveloped sites at the Evergrande Technology Tourism City on November 16, according to a statement by the district's Planning and Natural Resources Bureau.

news.title: Spain to approve mortgage support for more than one million households
news.para: The new measures are expected to be approved at a cabinet meeting on Tuesday pending final negotiations with banking associations, the ministry said.

news.title: Canada's Home Capital to go private in C$1.7 billion deal with Smith Financial
news.para: Its shares surged 57% to $42.45, inching closer to the offer price of C$44 per share as part of the all-cash deal with the family office of financial entrepreneur Stephen Smith. The offer was nearly 63% premium to Home Capital's last closing price.

news.title: Sunac China Holdings plans to extend onshore bonds maturity: Sources
news.para: Sunac earlier this year extended repayment for a 4-billion yuan bond. It is now proposing to further extend the repayment of 3.4 billion, the unpaid amount of this tranche, by three years and nine months to September 2026, said the sources.

news.title: Rajasthan CM approves Jaipur metro extension from Badi Chaupar to Transport Nagar
news.para: With this, Jaipur Metro will be extended 2.85km towards Walled City side. This extension will have 2.26km of underground tracks and 0.59km of elevated tracks.

news.title: Pune: 8,500 property owners get notice for excess water use
news.para: Binwade said that as per the new standards, water consumption of 150 litres per head per day is allowed. But in some cases, this usage is around 1,000 litres per head per day.

news.title: Whistleblower who exposed Kalyan-Dombivli RERA scam records his statement before court
news.para: After Patil exposed scam, a case was registered against 65 builders in Ramnagar and Manpada police stations in Dombivli.

news.title: Only 6% brick kilns in Uttarakhand have green clearance: Pollution watchdog
news.para: Pollution control board officials said 16 out of the 255 kilns were using the central pollution control board recommended "zigzag" technology.
